HEADWORD: Mesogaster
<hw>Mes`o*gas"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>me`sos</grk> middle + <?/ belly.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The fold of peritoneum connecting the stomach with the dorsal wall
of the abdominal cavity; the mesogastrium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

